dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init columns.searchPanes.combiner` paramater is undefined, meaning that as standard the pane use the title of the column for it's header.


        As standard, SearchPanes will set the headers of the pane based on the title of the corresponding column. This option allows for the header of the pane to be customised. 





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:true,
        dom: 'Sfrtip',
        columnDefs:[
            {
                searchPanes: {
                    header: 'Length of Life'
                },
                targets: [3]
            }
        ]
    });
});
